quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  88,1,"Has there come to you the narration of the overwhelming (i.e. the Day of Resurrection)?"
  88,2,"Some faces, that Day will be humiliated (in the Hell-fire, i.e. the faces of all disbelievers, Jews and Christians).{1}",footnotes:1:1
  88,3,"Labouring (hard in the worldly life by worshipping others besides Allâh), weary (in the Hereafter with humility and disgrace).{1}",footnotes:1:1
  88,4,"They will enter in the hot blazing Fire."
  88,5,"They will be given to drink from a boiling spring,"
  88,6,"No food will there be for them but a poisonous thorny plant,"
  88,7,"Which will neither nourish nor avail against hunger."
  88,8,"(Other) faces that Day will be joyful,"
  88,9,"Glad with their endeavour (for their good deeds which they did in this world, along with the true Faith of Islâmic Monotheism).{1}",footnotes:1:1
  88,10,"In a lofty Paradise."